ich was specific to caves had developed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCaveszGreat Britain. 0aHuman remains (Archaeology)zGreat Britain. 0aNeolithic periodzGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Archaeology.2bisacsh  aActor-network theory.  aAgency.  aBritain.  aCave sedimentology.  aCaves.  aFunerary Archaeology.  aNeolithic burial.  aObject biography.  aTaphonomy.1 aPeterson, Rick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packagez978311128249740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611887540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526118875423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526118875/original  a978-3-11-128249-7  Manchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packageb2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles